{"id":806,"date":"2022-01-17T14:39:29","date_gmt":"2022-01-17T14:39:29","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=806"},"modified":"2022-01-17T14:39:35","modified_gmt":"2022-01-17T14:39:35","slug":"process-script-inputs-1-2-etc","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/?p=806","title":{"rendered":"Process script inputs ($1, $2, etc.)"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><strong>What are the script inputs? <\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Arguments passed to a script are processed in the same order in which they\u2019re sent. The indexing of the arguments starts at one, and the first argument can be accessed inside the script using\u00a0<em>$1<\/em>. Similarly, the second argument can be accessed using\u00a0<em>$2,<\/em>\u00a0and so on. The positional parameter refers to this representation of the arguments using their position.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s try this on an example<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"alignleft size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"278\" height=\"129\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-114.png?resize=278%2C129&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-807\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-114.png?w=278&amp;ssl=1 278w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-114.png?resize=24%2C11&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-114.png?resize=36%2C17&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-114.png?resize=48%2C22&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 278px) 100vw, 278px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"572\" height=\"103\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-115.png?resize=572%2C103&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-808\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-115.png?w=572&amp;ssl=1 572w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-115.png?resize=300%2C54&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-115.png?resize=24%2C4&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-115.png?resize=36%2C6&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-115.png?resize=48%2C9&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 572px) 100vw, 572px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As you can see I&#8217;ve started our little script with some input variables (Filip, male, 25) and they are automatically marked with the input number ($1, $2, $3).<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Argument $0 <\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As you could probably notice, we&#8217;ve started with number $1 and that is very unusual in programming world because everything starts with 0. The reason for this is that, the $0 serves some purpose.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>$0 is an argument that returns the name of the file it&#8217;s being executed in, let me demonstrate.  <\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"alignleft size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"346\" height=\"76\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-116.png?resize=346%2C76&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-809\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-116.png?w=346&amp;ssl=1 346w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-116.png?resize=300%2C66&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-116.png?resize=24%2C5&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-116.png?resize=36%2C8&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-116.png?resize=48%2C11&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 346px) 100vw, 346px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"447\" height=\"60\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-117.png?resize=447%2C60&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-810\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-117.png?w=447&amp;ssl=1 447w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-117.png?resize=300%2C40&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-117.png?resize=24%2C3&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-117.png?resize=36%2C5&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-117.png?resize=48%2C6&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 447px) 100vw, 447px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Argument $#<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><code>$#<\/code>\u00a0is a special variable in\u00a0<code>bash<\/code>, that expands to the number of arguments (positional parameters) i.e.\u00a0<code>$1, $2 ...<\/code>\u00a0passed to the script in question or the shell in case of argument directly passed to the shell. The argument $0 aka the name of the script\/file doesn&#8217;t count into this number.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"481\" height=\"144\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-118.png?resize=481%2C144&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-811\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-118.png?w=481&amp;ssl=1 481w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-118.png?resize=300%2C90&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-118.png?resize=24%2C7&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-118.png?resize=36%2C11&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-118.png?resize=48%2C14&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 481px) 100vw, 481px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"543\" height=\"105\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-119.png?resize=543%2C105&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-812\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-119.png?w=543&amp;ssl=1 543w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-119.png?resize=300%2C58&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-119.png?resize=24%2C5&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-119.png?resize=36%2C7&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-119.png?resize=48%2C9&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 543px) 100vw, 543px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Arguments &amp;# and $*<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>These are very similar but slightly different, so I&#8217;ll try to explain them in one take.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><code>*<\/code>&nbsp;Expands to the positional parameters, starting from one. When the expansion occurs within double quotes, it expands to a single word with the value of each parameter separated by the first character of the IFS special variable. That is,&nbsp;<code>\"$*\"<\/code>&nbsp;is equivalent to&nbsp;<code>\"$1c$2c...\"<\/code>, where&nbsp;<code>c<\/code>&nbsp;is the first character of the value of the IFS variable. If IFS is unset, the parameters are separated by spaces. If IFS is null, the parameters are joined without intervening separators.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><code>@<\/code>\u00a0Expands to the positional parameters, starting from one. When the expansion occurs within double quotes, each parameter expands to a separate word. That is,\u00a0<code>\"$@\"<\/code>\u00a0is equivalent to\u00a0<code>\"$1\"<\/code>\u00a0<code>\"$2\"<\/code>\u00a0&#8230; If the double-quoted expansion occurs within a word, the expansion of the first parameter is joined with the beginning part of the original word, and the expansion of the last parameter is joined with the last part of the original word. When there are no positional parameters,\u00a0<code>\"$@\"<\/code>\u00a0and\u00a0<code>$@<\/code>\u00a0expand to nothing (i.e., they are removed)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>TLDR they both lists all used variables in slightly different way.<\/p><\/blockquote>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Real life example<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The script below will list all the input arguments used, otherwise it will print &#8220;no arguments used&#8221; to the terminal.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image is-style-default\"><figure class=\"alignleft size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"324\" height=\"244\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-120.png?resize=324%2C244&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-814\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-120.png?w=324&amp;ssl=1 324w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-120.png?resize=300%2C226&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-120.png?resize=24%2C18&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-120.png?resize=36%2C27&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-120.png?resize=48%2C36&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 324px) 100vw, 324px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full is-style-default\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"491\" height=\"136\" src=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-121.png?resize=491%2C136&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-815\" srcset=\"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-121.png?w=491&amp;ssl=1 491w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-121.png?resize=300%2C83&amp;ssl=1 300w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-121.png?resize=24%2C7&amp;ssl=1 24w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-121.png?resize=36%2C10&amp;ssl=1 36w, https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/image-121.png?resize=48%2C13&amp;ssl=1 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 491px) 100vw, 491px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" \/><\/figure>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>What are the script inputs? Arguments passed to a script are processed in the same [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":760,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"nf_dc_page":"","om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"_mi_skip_tracking":false},"categories":[219],"tags":[302,301,299,303,234,300,298,220],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https:\/\/i0.wp.com\/thetechcorner.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/rhsa-create-simple-shell-scripts-2.png?fit=1280%2C720&ssl=1","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/806"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcomments&post=806"}],"version-history":[{"count":2,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/806\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":816,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/posts\/806\/revisions\/816"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=\/wp\/v2\/media\/760"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fmedia&parent=806"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Fcategories&post=806"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/thetechcorner.org\/index.php?rest_route=%2Fwp%2Fv2%2Ftags&post=806"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}